Defining a Data Type:
    You can define a datatype for variables and arguments
    Is related to Type Hints by showing the dev hints on what to expect
    
    ex_ Defining an argument data type as a class |
    from file_name import Class_Name
    class New_Class:
        def __init__(self, argument_name:Class_Name):
    
    ex_ Defining variable datatype |
    age: int

    ex_ Defining function return's datatype |
    def function_name(arg:datatype) -> bool:
        if arg ....:
            return True
        else:
            return False